			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Nerfing and AEing<a name="53038"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 21 04 1:26 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>As any of us might be, I've been looking for a faster way than grouping to grind out a few useful AA's, and naturally I turned to the amazing world of AE kiting, since swarming in PoN usually yields about the same as a decent group might. Ooh, the amazing rumors of bards getting more than entire AA's in the span of a 15 minute kite, how enticing to see.
<br />

<br />
So I read up, do my research as any good bardess would do. I read guide upon guide, little posts like &quot;Where is your favorite spot to solo&quot; and the like, and I feel confident that if they can do it, I can too.
<br />

<br />
When I first started practicing I was camping that awful half elf mask, so I felt safe in AEing the whole bandit camp, which were all greens, just to practice the techniques I had read about. It went off without a hitch, how wonderful for me!
<br />

<br />
Getting braver, I head to PoN and AE about 10 spiders / ravens (the trees have long reach!) It works out well enough, so I decide to grind to 65 then try my hand with the golems and things in Valor!
<br />

<br />
Trying to be careful, I only pull about 5 or so golems and hit DA for a nice autocircle. I manage to get them to about 80% and then I get stunned somehow and ruthlessly beat. Rez, rinse, repeat? Died about 3 times, never able to get the golems past 75% health before something happens and I get massacred. I tried again this morning with only slightly better luck, getting killed twice more before finally asking some fellow bards on the server what they think about AEing.
<br />

<br />
The resounding reply: &quot;Oh, I don't AE since the nerf&quot; 
<br />

<br />
Well, that certianly makes me the a$, doesnt it? Could I get some reassurance or something?? AEing or no?</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
