<br />

<br />
Number 1 - start out fast with something like TDoK to get ur auto circle going.  Ur circle will be much too big with it and DDD will hit half the time with other PBAEs hitting only a fraction of the time.
<br />

<br />
Number 2 - Switch to something with a 2.0 mod for drums (such as Combine Drum or the Gouche thingy).  Then pulse the selo's again.  When mobs are running at normal speed (gunthak, dulak, nadox) the switch to 2.0 will put u in the proper circle so that all of ur AEs hit.
<br />

<br />
Number 3 - Make sure u switch the right insturment with the right things.  Problem i had starting out was things like i would accidentally not equip a drum and pulse selos and slow down heavily and run directly into my train (ouch)
<br />

<br />
Number 4 - The final thing would be to do the following, filter off bard songs, emotes, say text, hits, misses, clip plane to 0%, and switch into the view that watches u from the side at the middle of where ur runnin and turnin this way ur train is right behind ur camera and u dont get lag from that.  Finally turn off spell particle effects.
<br />

<br />
Following these tips i am able to auto circle a 35 mob kite in dulak with a p3 855mhz processor and 256MB of ram.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
